#, no-wrap
msgid "Plugins Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "The management of plugins in NvChad 2.0 is done by [folke/lazy.nvim](https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim), this plugin is installed during the first installation from the bootstrap procedure. The plugin allows you to perform all common operations on plugins, such as installing, updating, etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Lazy Nvim](../images/lazy_nvim.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Management of all operations on plugins from a unified interface.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optimized plugin performance due to caching and compilation of Lua module bytecode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Automatic check and installation of missing plugins at startup, a very useful feature when transferring a configuration from one machine to another.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Profiler for consulting plugin loading times. Allows you to monitor and troubleshoot problems caused by faulty plugins.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Synchronization of plugins across multiple workstations by storing the revision of all installed plugins in the _lazy-lock.json_ file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "_lazy.nvim_ integrates an environment health check feature that can be invoked with the command `:checkhealth lazy`. The command should return something like this in a new buffer:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "lazy: require(\"lazy.health\").check()\n"
"========================================================================\n"
"## lazy.nvim\n"
"  - OK: Git installed\n"
"  - OK: no existing packages found by other package managers\n"
"  - OK: packer_compiled.lua not found\n"
"  - WARNING: {nvim-lspconfig}: overriding <config>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Although not strictly necessary, checking the build environment before we start working on our custom configuration allows us to exclude this variable from any errors or malfunctions that might occur in the plugins themselves or in writing their configurations. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "It may also be interesting to consult the inline help provided by the plugin itself. To open it we can use the `:Lazy help` command or invoke it from the plugin interface by typing <kbd>?</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Lazy Help](../images/lazy_help.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Help provides an introduction to interface navigation, controls, and their functions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now after checking out the environment and gaining basic knowledge we can move on to creating our own configuration. The purpose clearly is to add functionality to the editor to meet our needs, and since this is achieved by including plugins in the NvChad configuration we will start by adding a plugin.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Inserting a Plugin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "    In these examples it is assumed that during the installation of NvChad you chose to create the `custom` folder structure with the _template chadrc_.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "While management of installed plugins can be conveniently performed from the _lazy.nvim_ interface, inserting a new plugin requires manual editing of the **custom/plugins.lua** file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "In this example we will install the [natecraddock/workspaces.nvim](https://github.com/natecraddock/workspaces.nvim) plugin. This plugin allows you to save and later use work sessions (workspaces) so you can access them quickly. We open the file with:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "nvim ~/.config/nvim/lua/custom/plugins.lua\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "and we insert the following code after the plugin _better-escape.nvim_:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "    -- Workspaces\n"
"    {\n"
"        \"natecraddock/workspaces.nvim\",\n"
"        cmd = { \"WorkspacesList\", \"WorkspacesAdd\", \"WorkspacesOpen\", \"WorkspacesRemove\" },\n"
"        config = function()\n"
"            require(\"workspaces\").setup {\n"
"        hooks = {\n"
"            open = \"Telescope find_files\",\n"
"        },\n"
"      }\n"
"    end,\n"
"    },\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the file is saved we will receive a notice requesting our approval: \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "# Config Change Detected. Reloading...\n\n"
"> - **changed**: `plugins.lua`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:90
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is thanks to the mechanism built into _lazy.nvim_ that checks the status of the plugins and its configurations and thus allows operations on the plugins to be performed without having to exit the editor, an operation that was necessary with version 1.0.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "Clearly we will answer \"yes.\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:94
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now if we open the plugin manager with the `:Lazy` command we will find that our plugin has been recognized and is ready to be installed. To install it, simply type <kbd>I</kbd> \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Install Plugin](../images/lazy_install.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "At this point it will be _lazy.nvim_ that will take care of downloading the repository in the path **.local/share/nvim/lazy/** and performing the build. Once the installation is finished we will have a new folder named _workspaces.nvim_:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ".local/share/nvim/lazy/workspaces.nvim/\n"
"├── CHANGELOG.md\n"
"├── doc\n"
"│   ├── tags\n"
"│   └── workspaces.txt\n"
"├── LICENSE\n"
"├── lua\n"
"│   ├── telescope\n"
"│   │   └── _extensions\n"
"│   │       └── workspaces.lua\n"
"│   └── workspaces\n"
"│       ├── init.lua\n"
"│       └── util.lua\n"
"├── README.md\n"
"└── stylua.toml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "We will now have plugin functionality that can be invoked with the commands set in the array:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "cmd = { \"WorkspacesList\", \"WorkspacesAdd\", \"WorkspacesOpen\", \"WorkspacesRemove\" },\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:124
#, no-wrap
msgid "Input also involves adding a string to the _lazy-lock.json_ file for status tracking and subsequent updates. The function of the _lazy-lock.json_ file will be described in the corresponding section below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "  \"workspaces.nvim\": { \"branch\": \"master\", \"commit\": \"dd9574c8a6fbd4910bf298fcd1175a0222e9a09d\" },\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "Removing a plugin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "As with installation, removing a plugin from the configuration also goes through manual editing of the _custom/plugins.lua_ file. In this example we are going to remove the plugin [TimUntersberger/neogit](https://github.com/TimUntersberger/neogit) this plugin allows a management of git repositories directly from the editor.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The choice of plugin is purely random. The plugin used for the example has no problems working in NvChad.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "We open our editor and remove the plugin from the configuration. This can be done conveniently by selecting the four rows to be deleted with the mouse and then pressing <kbd>x</kbd> to delete them and <kbd>CTRL</kbd> + <kbd>s</kbd> to save the file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Remove Plugin](../images/remove_plugin_01.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "Again we will receive a notice about the modification of the _plugins.lua_ file to which we will answer \"yes\" and once we open _Lazy_ we will have our plugin marked as to be removed. Removal is done by pressing the <kbd>X</kbd> key.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:143
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Lazy Clean](../images/remove_plugin_02.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "Removing a plugin basically consists of removing the folder created during installation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "Updating Plugins"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the plugins are installed and configured they are managed independently by _lazy.nvim_. To check for updates, just open the manager and type <kbd>C</kbd>. _Lazy_ will check the repositories of the installed plugins (_git fetch_) and then it will present us with a list of updatable plugins that, once checked, can be updated all in one go with <kbd>U</kbd> or individually after selecting them with <kbd>u</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:151
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Lazy Check](../images/lazy_check.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:155
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Even if not present in the screenshot above, if there are plugins with commits including \"breaking changes\" these will be displayed first.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is also the possibility of running the entire update cycle with just the `Sync` command. From the interface by typing <kbd>S</kbd> or with the command `:Lazy sync` we will invoke the function, which consists of the concatenation of `install` + `clean` + `update`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:159
#, no-wrap
msgid "The update process, whether done individually or cumulatively, will also modify the _lazy-lock.json_ file. In particular, commits will be modified to synchronize them with the state of the repository on GitHub. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:160
#, no-wrap
msgid "Additional Features"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:163
#, no-wrap
msgid "In writing the plugin, special attention was paid to performance and code efficiency, and to give us a way to evaluate the startup times of the various plugins. We are provided with a _profiler_ that can be invoked with the `:Lazy profile` command or with the <kbd>P</kbd> key from the interface.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Lazy Profiler](../images/lazy_profile.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:167
#, no-wrap
msgid "Here we can see the loading times of the various plugins that can be sorted with the key combination <knd>CTRL</kbd> + <kbd>s</kbd> by entry in the configuration or by loading time. We also have the possibility to perform searches on the loading time of plugins by setting a minimum threshold in milliseconds with the combination <kbd>CTRL</kbd> + <kbd>f</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/nvchad_ui/plugins_manager.md:169
#, no-wrap
